                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On the afternoon of March 25, King Abdullah Ibn el-Hussein handed the Chargé in
                    Transjordan, Wells Stabler, a message which he requested be urgently transmitted
                    to President Truman. The message dealt with the subject of territory occupied by
                    Iraqi forces and with the request of Israel for a modification of the present
                    front between Iraqi and Israeli forces. The message was transmitted to the
                    Department by Amman in telegram 132, March 25, 8 p. m. (867N.01/3–2549)</p>
            </div>
